[Lychee (_Litchi chinensis_), longan (_Dimocarpus longan_) and rambutan (_Nephelium lappaceum_) of the family _Sapindaceae_ are important fruit and cash crops in parts of Asia.

The symptoms described above are not sufficient for identifying a likely pathogen. Reliable diagnosis is crucial for designing control or management strategies for the affected farmers.

